## Code Conventions

### Imports

Import order (handled by ESLint):

1. React and external libraries
2. Internal components (alias `components/`)
3. Internal hooks
4. Types (alias `types/`)
5. Local styles (CSS Modules)

```tsx
import { useState } from 'react';

import classNames from 'classnames';
import { CvElement } from 'types/CvElement';

import styles from './Component.module.css';
```

### TypeScript

- Use `interface` for component props
- Export types alongside components
- Avoid `any`, use `unknown` if needed
- Optional props should have default values in destructuring

### Naming

| Element             | Convention             | Example                               |
| ------------------- | ---------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Components          | PascalCase             | `Button`, `ProductCard`               |
| Props interface     | PascalCase + Props     | `ButtonProps`                         |
| Component files     | PascalCase             | `Button.tsx`                          |
| Style files         | PascalCase + module    | `Button.module.css`                   |
| CSS Modules classes | camelCase              | `.root`, `.fullWidth`, `.primary`     |
| CSS Variables       | kebab-case with prefix | `--cv-button-bg`, `--cv-button-color` |
| Hooks               | camelCase with "use"   | `useClickOutside`                     |

