## CSS Modules

This library uses **CSS Modules** for locally scoped styles.

### Import

```tsx
import styles from './Component.module.css';
```

### Class usage

```tsx
// Single class
<div className={styles.root}>

// Multiple classes with classnames
<div className={classNames(styles.root, styles[variant], {
  [styles.fullWidth]: isFullWidth,
})}>
```

### CSS naming conventions

```css
/* Component root class */
.root { }

/* Variants - applied via styles[variant] */
.primary { }
.secondary { }

/* Sizes - applied via styles[size] */
.S { }
.M { }

/* Boolean modifiers */
.fullWidth { }
.disabled { }
.checked { }

/* Inner elements */
.label { }
.icon { }
.container { }
```

### CSS Variables

Component-scoped CSS variables use the `--cv-` prefix. Their values **must** reference **semantic design tokens** — never primitive tokens.

**Allowed references:**
- Semantic tokens: `--color-*`, `--spacing-*`, `--corner-radius-*`, `--font-size-*`, `--line-height-*`, `--icon-size-*`
- Custom component variables: `--cv-*`

**Forbidden references (primitives):**
- `--size-*`, `--brand-light-*`, `--brand-dark-*`, `--neutrals-*`, `--system-error-*`, `--system-success-*`, `--system-warning-*`, `--system-info-*`, `--interactivity-states-*`, `--gradients-*`, `--font-family-*`, `--font-weight-*`

```css
/* Correct — semantic tokens */
.root {
  --cv-button-background: var(--color-fill-common-brand);
  --cv-button-color: var(--color-text-inverted);

  background: var(--cv-button-background);
  color: var(--cv-button-color);
}

/* Wrong — primitive tokens */
.root {
  --cv-button-background: var(--brand-dark-50);    /* use --color-fill-common-brand */
  --cv-button-color: var(--neutrals-white-00);     /* use --color-text-inverted */
}
```

