## Accessibility

- Use appropriate ARIA roles
- Include `aria-label` when needed
- Support keyboard navigation
- Maintain adequate color contrast
- Use semantic elements (`button`, `input`, etc.)

---

## Testing

### Preferred Queries (Testing Library)

1. `getByRole` - Best for accessibility
2. `getByLabelText` - For labeled inputs
3. `getByText` - For text content
4. `getByTestId` - Last resort

### Assertions for CSS Modules

```tsx
// Verify classes with CSS Modules (hashed names)
expect(button.className).toMatch(/primary/);
expect(button.className).toMatch(/fullWidth/);

// Verify attributes
expect(button).toHaveAttribute('data-qa', 'test-qa');
expect(button).toHaveAttribute('id', 'test-id');
```

### Mocks

```tsx
// Function mock
const handleClick = vi.fn();

// ResizeObserver mock (already configured in vitest.setup.ts)
// No need to mock manually
```

