## Storybook

- All stories are centered by default (`layout: 'centered'`)
- Global font: Roboto
- Document props with `argTypes`, including descriptions and default values
- Create stories for each important variant with its own description

### Component documentation via README.md

Every component **must** have a `README.md` file in its folder. The README is imported as a raw string and used as the Storybook docs description — **do not** write inline component descriptions in the story file.

```tsx
import { Meta, StoryFn } from '@storybook/react';

import { ComponentName, type ComponentNameProps } from './ComponentName';
import README from './README.md?raw';

export default {
  title: 'Components/ComponentName',
  component: ComponentName,
  parameters: {
    docs: {
      description: {
        component: README,
      },
    },
  },
  // ...argTypes
} as Meta<typeof ComponentName>;
```

The `?raw` suffix tells Vite to import the file as a plain string. This keeps documentation in a single Markdown source of truth shared by Storybook and any other tooling.

